 Laetitia Dagan, an Assistant Director of Administration at the State House, Abuja, has been killed in her residence by unknown persons. Dagan, who was 47 before her death, was gruesomely murdered in her home around 11pm on Monday after she got home from the day’s work. Confirming the death of Dagan, the Permanent Secretary, State House, Abuja, Jalal Arabi, said that the deceased worked in her office on Monday till 8pm. He described the killing of Dagan as “a painful loss, not only to her immediate family, but also the entire State House.” He also said that Dagan was “a dedicated, hard-working officer, and we all feel pained by her untimely death.” Arabi expressed confidence that the police will fish out the killers and the law will take its course.